The paper deals with voice conversion, which is a subfield of speech processing and natural language processing. The use of Cycle-GAN and sequence-to-sequence models suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The focus on phoneme posteriorgram sequences and prosody suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of sound and music computing (cs.SD).
